      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW DANGER (1) was a winner two back when prominent throughout then got further back last time and could manage only a 4.5 lengths 4th at Shepparton (22.48). Rates on top in this line up. PAW REVY (2) finds it hard to win but has a consistent overall record, having placed nine of 17 career runs. Has been in the money the last three starts, the latest when third (22.46) at this track. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Expected to be in this for a long way. BROTHER BUB (7) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Has hit the frame at his last four runs, the latest finishing second (22.41) at this track. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Leading player again. PAW GAMMA (8) defied the market to win last start and cannot be ruled out.",
